Q1. Initialize a new repository using Git and commit a README.md file
================================================================================

STEP 1: Install Git (if not already installed)
-----------------------------------------------
sudo apt update
sudo apt install git -y
git --version

STEP 2: Configure Git (first time setup)
-----------------------------------------
git config --global user.name "YourName"
git config --global user.email "youremail@example.com"

STEP 3: Create a project folder and initialize Git
----------------------------------------------------
mkdir my-project
cd my-project
git init

STEP 4: Create a README.md file
---------------------------------
echo "# My Project" > README.md
echo "This is a Hello World project." >> README.md

STEP 5: Stage and commit the file
-----------------------------------
git add README.md
git status
git commit -m "Initial commit - added README.md"

STEP 6: Verify the commit
---------------------------
git log --oneline


