Q6. Run the Docker container and access the application in the browser
================================================================================

STEP 1: Make sure Docker image exists
---------------------------------------
docker images
# Should show: hello-world-app

STEP 2: Run the Docker container
----------------------------------
docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name mycontainer hello-world-app

   Flags explained:
   -d   = detached mode (runs in background)
   -p   = port mapping (host:container)
   --name = give container a name

STEP 3: Check if container is running
---------------------------------------
docker ps

STEP 4: Access in browser
---------------------------
Open browser -> http://localhost:5000
You will see: Hello World from Docker!

STEP 5: View container logs
-----------------------------
docker logs mycontainer

STEP 6: Stop the container (when done)
----------------------------------------
docker stop mycontainer


