STEP 2: Get Jenkins initial password
--------------------------------------
sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword

STEP 3: Setup Jenkins
----------------------
- Open browser -> http://localhost:8080
- Enter the initial password
- Install suggested plugins
- Create admin user
- Click "Start using Jenkins"

STEP 4: Create a Pipeline project
-----------------------------------
- Click "New Item"
- Enter name: hello-world-pipeline
- Select "Pipeline"
- Click OK

STEP 5: Configure Pipeline Script
-----------------------------------
In the Pipeline section, select "Pipeline script" and enter:

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Clone') {
            steps {
                echo 'Cloning repository...'
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                echo 'Building application...'
            }
        }
        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                echo 'Running tests...'
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy') {
            steps {
                echo 'Deploying application...'
            }
        }
    }
}

STEP 6: Save and Build
-----------------------
- Click "Save"
- Click "Build Now"
- Click on the build number -> "Console Output"
- You should see all stages completing successfully


