Q12. Configure Jenkins pipeline to pull code from GitHub
================================================================================

STEP 1: Make sure Git plugin is installed in Jenkins
------------------------------------------------------
- Jenkins Dashboard -> Manage Jenkins -> Plugin Manager
- Check "Git Plugin" is installed (usually installed by default)

STEP 2: Create a Jenkinsfile in your project
---------------------------------------------
cat > Jenkinsfile << 'EOF'
pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Clone Repository') {
            steps {
                git branch: 'main',
                    url: 'https://github.com/YourUsername/my-project.git'
            }
        }
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'echo Building the application...'
                sh 'pip install -r requirements.txt || true'
            }
        }
        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                sh 'echo Running tests...'
            }
        }
        stage('Run') {
            steps {
                sh 'echo Application deployed successfully!'
            }
        }
    }
}
EOF

STEP 3: Push Jenkinsfile to GitHub
------------------------------------
git add Jenkinsfile
git commit -m "Added Jenkinsfile for CI/CD"
git push origin main

STEP 4: Configure Jenkins Job to use GitHub
---------------------------------------------
- Jenkins Dashboard -> New Item -> Pipeline -> OK
- Under "Pipeline" section:
  - Definition: "Pipeline script from SCM"
  - SCM: Git
  - Repository URL: https://github.com/YourUsername/my-project.git
  - Branch: */main
  - Script Path: Jenkinsfile
- Click Save

STEP 5: Build and Verify
--------------------------
- Click "Build Now"
- Click on build -> Console Output
- You should see all stages running and code pulled from GitHub


