Q15. Create pipeline stages in Jenkins to build and run the application
================================================================================

STEP 1: Create app.py
----------------------
cat > app.py << 'EOF'
from flask import Flask
app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello():
    return "<h1>Hello World from Jenkins Pipeline!</h1>"

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run(host='0.0.0.0', port=5000)
EOF

STEP 2: Create Dockerfile
--------------------------
cat > Dockerfile << 'EOF'
FROM python:3.9-slim
WORKDIR /app
COPY requirements.txt .
RUN pip install -r requirements.txt
COPY . .
EXPOSE 5000
CMD ["python", "app.py"]
EOF

STEP 3: Create Jenkinsfile with multiple stages
------------------------------------------------
cat > Jenkinsfile << 'EOF'
pipeline {
    agent any

    stages {
        stage('Clone') {
            steps {
                echo 'Stage 1: Cloning repository...'
                git url: 'https://github.com/YourUsername/my-project.git', branch: 'main'
            }
        }

        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps {
                echo 'Stage 2: Building Docker image...'
                sh 'docker build -t hello-world-app .'
            }
        }

        stage('Test') {
            steps {
                echo 'Stage 3: Running tests...'
                sh 'docker run --rm hello-world-app python -c "import flask; print(flask.__version__)"'
            }
        }

        stage('Run Application') {
            steps {
                echo 'Stage 4: Running the application...'
                sh 'docker stop myapp || true'
                sh 'docker rm myapp || true'
                sh 'docker run -d -p 5000:5000 --name myapp hello-world-app'
                echo 'Application running at http://localhost:5000'
            }
        }
    }

    post {
        success {
            echo 'Pipeline completed successfully!'
        }
        failure {
            echo 'Pipeline failed!'
        }
    }
}
EOF

STEP 4: Push to GitHub
-----------------------
git add .
git commit -m "Added Jenkins pipeline stages"
git push origin main

STEP 5: Configure Jenkins
--------------------------
- New Item -> Pipeline -> OK
- Pipeline -> SCM -> Git
- Repo URL: https://github.com/YourUsername/my-project.git
- Branch: */main
- Script Path: Jenkinsfile
- Save -> Build Now

STEP 6: Monitor Stages
-----------------------
- Click on the build
- You will see Stage View showing all 4 stages
- Click "Console Output" to see detailed logs


================================================================================
                    QUICK REFERENCE CHEAT SHEET
================================================================================

GIT COMMANDS:
  git init                          Initialize new repo
  git add .                         Stage all files
  git commit -m "message"           Commit changes
  git branch                        List branches
  git checkout -b branch-name       Create and switch branch
  git merge branch-name             Merge branch into current
  git push origin main              Push to GitHub
  git remote add origin <url>       Link to GitHub repo

DOCKER COMMANDS:
  docker build -t name .            Build image from Dockerfile
  docker images                     List images
  docker run -d -p 5000:5000 name   Run container
  docker ps                         List running containers
  docker stop container-name        Stop container
  docker rm container-name          Remove container
  docker push username/imagename    Push to Docker Hub
  docker pull username/imagename    Pull from Docker Hub

JENKINS PIPELINE STAGES:
  Clone -> Build -> Test -> Deploy

DEFAULT PORTS:
  Flask App  -> 5000
  Node.js    -> 3000
  Jenkins    -> 8080

